GEMTEC Consulting Engineers and Scientist Limited. is seeking applicants for the position of junior field technician/technologist in our Petawawa location. Effective written and verbal communication skills along with the ability to work both independently or within a multi-disciplinary team are considered essential assets.
Responsibilities will include:
Provide field testing and inspections for various projects including foundation inspections, compaction testing and concrete testing;
Conduct field surveying using total station and global positioning system (GPS);
Compile and tabulate technical data for use in technical reports.
Successful candidates will have the following qualities/credentials:
"Team Player" capable of working both independently or as part of a larger team to complete assigned tasks;
Strong time management skills;
Excellent communication skills;
Willingness to travel throughout eastern Ontario and work in variable climatic conditions often for extended hours; possess ability to periodically lift heavy objects and navigate uneven terrain.
Working knowledge of Microsoft office products (Word, Excel, Project).
A valid G class driver’s license.
Prior training in WHMIS, First Aid/CPR, and working at heights is considered an asset.
GEMTEC Consulting Engineers and Scientist Limited offers a family friendly work environment and a competitive salary and benefits package. If you are interested in developing your career at a 100% employee owned firm that emphasizes and recognizes employee participation and contributions, please submit your resume to ottawa@gemtec.ca.
Although we are grateful to all applicants for their interest, we regret that only those candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.

