Department: Research and Development
Location: 101 College Street, Toronto, Ontario, Canada
Salary: Based on level of experience

About Geneseeq
Geneseeq is a health solutions company that specializes in personalized cancer care and aims to provide treatment solutions based on the comprehensive analyses of patients’ genomic profile. The company is translating scientific knowledge into the well-being of the patients. Its mission is to bring precision cancer care to patients through the combination of next-generation sequencing (NGS) and up-to-date cancer knowledge base. Geneseeq is currently headquartered both in Toronto, Ontario, Canada, and Nanjing, Jiangsu, China, with more than 800 employees.
Position Description
We are seeking a highly motivated and experienced Bioinformatics Scientist in the Department of Research and Development. The successful candidate will focus on the analysis of large NGS datasets with in-depth knowledge of data-handling and sufficient knowledge of cancer genomics. This position will provide ample opportunities for professional development and the acquisition of cutting-edge skills in basic and translational cancer genomics research, research planning and strategy, and data analysis and interpretation.
Responsibilities include:
Identifies and explores signals relevant to early cancer detection from large-scale NGS data;
Develops and prototypes novel machine learning models for cancer signal detection in liquid biopsy;
Conducts and optimizes bioinformatic analysis of NGS data and various statistical analyses;
Records all analysis steps in an accurate, timely and clearly presented manner, and use this to prepare data summaries and reports as and when required;
Performs literature reviews, prepares data visualization, and drafts scientific publications and grant proposals;
Prepares conference abstracts, posters and presentations;
Supervises junior bioinformaticians;
Provides scientific support to customers and research collaborators;
Other duties as assigned.
Position requirements
PhD in bioinformatics, computational biology, data science, machine learning, statistics or a related discipline with over 5 years of research experience
Strong background with unix/linux tools and coding experience with PERL, PYTHON or related data analysis languages;
Solid understanding of statistics, expertise in R and Bioconductor;
Exposure to NGS data is mandatory with advanced knowledge of NGS platforms, datatype (FASTQ, BAM, VCF, MAF) and analysis tools;
A proven track record in the analysis of large “omics” data sets (e.g. RNA-seq, whole genome/exome sequencing and epigenomics data) and clinical NGS data sets;
Experienced with systematically designing, training, debugging, and evaluating machine learning models such as boosting ensemble methods, neural networks and deep learning;
Experienced developing and implementing deep learning methods, and going beyond packaged algorithms;
Experience in working with test-driven programming and version control is an asset;
Excellent written and oral communication skills and proven leadership abilities.
Excellent publication track record.
Only candidate selected for an interview will be contacted.

Data Analyst - Internal Audit-MON17447

Description

BOMBARDIER

At Bombardier, our employees work together to evolve mobility worldwide - one good idea at a time. If you have a good idea, we’ll provide the environment where it will thrive and grow into a great product or customer experience. Your ideas are our fuel.

In your role, you will:

Develop, improve and implement the department’s data analysis roadmap;

Identify and subsequently act on opportunities to analyze and visualize data at every phase of the audit process;

Identify relevant data for current and future needs; coordinate data extraction and updates in the source systems;

Expertly contribute to audit and advisory engagements by putting forward and executing data analysis scripts designed to increase the quality and efficiency of audits, in accordance with latest industry standards and changing practices;

Analyze and interpret outcomes of data analysis scripts; review outcomes with managers of audited units and make recommendations;

Develop data visualization reports (e.g. Power BI) to present information in a credible, compelling way;

Help with other team tasks, as requested.

Qualifications

As our ideal candidate,

You have 2 to 5 years of experience in internal auditing and/or business intelligence;

You have Bachelor’s degree in IT, business administration, management, accounting or a related field; Masters an asset

You have advanced knowledge of Excel, and data analysis and visualization tools (e.g.Power BI);

You have advanced knowledge of SQL, ACL, Alteryx, an asset;

You have knowledge of SAP, Concur, Salesforce systems;

You have CPA, CIA, CISA or CFE designation, an asset;

You have and understanding of industry best practices, especially those related to data modelling and standardization;

You have a keen sense of initiative, agility and adaptability in a constantly changing environment;

You have an analytical mindset with a talent for solving complex problems and formulating recommendations;

You have in-depth knowledge of Microsoft Office 365 tools (SharePoint, OneDrive, OneNote, Teams);

You have curiosity and business sense;

You have excellent written and spoken French and English;

You are a team player with strong interpersonal skills;

You are meticulous, organized and self-motivated;

You are available to travel up to 15% of the time.

Bombardier is an equal opportunity employer and encourages women, Aboriginal people, persons with disabilities and members of visible minorities to apply.

Whether your candidacy is moving on to the next step of the hiring process or not, we will keep you informed by email or by phone. Join us at careers.bombardier.com

