At PLB, the Data Analyst and Demand Planning, reporting to the Sales department, is responsible for developing a sales forecast by product for a horizon of 13 continuous periods based on product families and market trends. He also supports Marketing team as well as Logistics so that customer and market trends are understood and applied, sales forecasts are accurate, performance is measured by KPIs and post-mortem, while ensuring fluid communication between services impacted by forecasts, all the while taking into account operational constraints.
Specifically, he will be responsible for:
PLANNING THE DEMAND
Responsible for the demand side of the S&OP process;
Follow up with sales managers to obtain a sales forecast, as well as marketing for new products or promotions;
Establish sales forecasts, ensure follow-ups and keep the database up to date.
CARRY OUT MONITORING AND PRODUCE REPORTS
Create specific ad hoc reports to highlight current sales performance and communicate results;
Communicate anticipated activities to production planning, procurement, distribution, customer service;
Question and inform the stakeholders concerned about the results obtained;
Issue and monitor performance indicators.
PARTICIPATE IN SALES & OPERATIONS PLANNING (S&OP) PROCESS
Establish the definition, maintenance and use of efficient analysis tools;
Collect historical data and prepare necessary documents to facilitate S&OP meetings;
Support the execution of the demand planning process;
Track sales trends, budgets vs. forecasts vs. current orders, and KPIs
What are we looking for in our future co-worker?
Action-oriented and the internal and external customer;
Self-control, be able to clearly define one's priorities;
Great interpersonal communication skills, know how to negotiate, master problem solving;
Result-oriented and demonstrate autonomy.
SKILLS NECESSARY FOR THE POSITION
Bachelor's degree in administration, option management of operations and logistics, mathematics, statistics, commerce or related field;
3-5 years of experience in demand planning, data and analytics (consumer products industry, food industry is considered an asset)
Advanced knowledge of statistical forecasting methods;
Good knowledge of the supply chain and logistics;
