Bachelor’s degree. with 6 to 10 years of experience;
Master’s degree with 4 to 7 years of experience;
Profound knowledge of Microsoft products (including MS Dynamics and Power BI) and of SAP;
Knowledge of the aerospace aftermarket business;
Strong project management skills.
Focus on results;
Adaptability (ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced atmosphere);
Effective communication skills from shop-floor to executive level;
Field of studies : Aerodynamics Engineering, Aerospace Engineering, Mathematics Engineering, Physics Engineering, Computer Science, Applied Sciences
